        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-9 multiple-edit-warning">
        <div class="alert alert-warning" id="warning-e44f6d5b-64ad-4c4e-9a04-fe3cc77dc1ad">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.
        </div>
    </div>

        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-e44f6d5b-64ad-4c4e-9a04-fe3cc77dc1ad">
                Mr. Emrys Hughes
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-e44f6d5b-64ad-4c4e-9a04-fe3cc77dc1ad" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1954-01-26/debates/d92b8814-44eb-4242-839b-77d0bc62a067/CivilDefence(MinisterialResponsibility)#contribution-e44f6d5b-64ad-4c4e-9a04-fe3cc77dc1ad">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">asked the Prime Minister if, in view of the disclosures in the Report of the Select Committee on the inefficiency and inadequacy of Civil Defence measures to protect the civil population of this country in the event of atomic bomb attack, he will appoint a new Minister of Cabinet rank with the sole duty of dealing with the problems of Civil Defence.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-e44f6d5b-64ad-4c4e-9a04-fe3cc77dc1ad" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1954-01-26/debates/d92b8814-44eb-4242-839b-77d0bc62a067/CivilDefence(MinisterialResponsibility)#contribution-e44f6d5b-64ad-4c4e-9a04-fe3cc77dc1ad">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
</div>





<div class="content-item" id="contribution-02661f61-133f-49f1-b320-be63c9fa1b63">
    <div class="col-md-9 edit-fail-error">
        <div class="alert alert-danger" id="alert-02661f61-133f-49f1-b320-be63c9fa1b63">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>The edit just sent has not been saved.  The following error was returned:
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-9 multiple-edit-warning">
        <div class="alert alert-warning" id="warning-02661f61-133f-49f1-b320-be63c9fa1b63">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-info-sign"></span>This content has already been edited and is awaiting review.
        </div>
    </div>

        <div class="col-md-9 nohighlight member-container">
            <h2 class="memberLink col-md-9" id="member-link-02661f61-133f-49f1-b320-be63c9fa1b63">
                The Prime Minister (Sir Winston Churchill)
            </h2>
        </div>
            <div class="col-md-3 hidden-sm hidden-xs right-column ">
            <a href="#contribution-02661f61-133f-49f1-b320-be63c9fa1b63" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
               data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
               data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1954-01-26/debates/d92b8814-44eb-4242-839b-77d0bc62a067/CivilDefence(MinisterialResponsibility)#contribution-02661f61-133f-49f1-b320-be63c9fa1b63">
                <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div><span class="share-text">Share</span>
            </a>
        </div>

    


    <div class="inner">
        <div class="col-md-9 contribution content-container">



<p class="">No, Sir. Experience before, during and since the last war has shown conclusively that the main Civil Defence work is so closely linked with the maintenance of law and order and the work of local authorities that the Home Secretary and the Secretary of State for Scotland must be the focal points for preparations and for operational control in the event of war. There has, of course, to be close liaison between the fighting Services and <span id="1605" class="column-number" data-column-number="1605"></span> those engaged in Civil Defence, but this can be effectively secured, in our opinion, by consultations between Ministers and the services concerned.</p>                    <div class="hidden-md hidden-lg" style="padding-left: 0px;">
                        <a href="#contribution-02661f61-133f-49f1-b320-be63c9fa1b63" rel="popover" class="link-to-contribution link-to-contribution-mobile link-text" title="Share this contribution" data-placement="top"
                           data-hop-url-shorten-url="/UrlShortener/ShorternUrl"
                           data-hop-popover="http://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/1954-01-26/debates/d92b8814-44eb-4242-839b-77d0bc62a067/CivilDefence(MinisterialResponsibility)#contribution-02661f61-133f-49f1-b320-be63c9fa1b63">
                            <div class="share-icon">&nbsp;</div>&nbsp;Share
                        </a>
                    </div>

        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="clearfix"></div>
</div>





<div class="content-item" id="contribution-80b6d042-cb84-4572-9f09-26d992e4b1a8">
